BBC - Pembrokeshire: Coastal Lives 2of4 Episode2 (2013)



Episode 2 of 4
DURATION: 30 MINUTES
The Pembrokeshire coast path passes through some of the most breathtaking scenery in the world. But what is life like for the locals who live, work and play in this Welsh paradise? This series follows the people of the path through the hot summer of 2013.

In this programme, Pembrokeshire legend Auntie Vi Weston celebrates her 92nd birthday at her cafe in Bosherston. Buzz Knapp-Fisher makes his eco 'Loo with a View', and competition gets heated between the Milford pigeon racers as they send their young birds into their first big race of the year.
